Facebook’s messaging app WhatsApp on Thursday launched its WhatsApp Business app for Apple’s iOS operating system, allowing small businesses to communicate with customers through the platform. WhatsApp Business will be available for free download from the App Store in Brazil, Germany, Indonesia, India, Mexico, the UK and the US starting Thursday and will be rolled out around the world in the coming weeks, WhatsApp said https://blog.whatsapp.com/10000659/Bringing-the-WhatsApp-Business-App-To-iPhone. The service has been available on Android since last year and has over 5 million users.